:R-HSA-445989  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "NF-kappa-B is sequestered in the cytoplasm in a complex with inhibitor of NF-kappa-B (IkB). Almost all NF-kappa-B activation pathways are mediated by IkB kinase (IKK), which phosphorylates IkB resulting in dissociation of NF-kappa-B from the complex. This allows translocation of NF-kappa-B to the nucleus where it regulates gene expression." ;
        rdfs:label          "TAK1-dependent IKK and NF-kappa-B activation" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Fitzgerald, Katherine A, 2012-11-13" , "Reviewed: de Martin, R, 2022-05-04" , "Edited: Shamovsky, V, 2011-08-12" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Napetschnig, Johanna, 2012-11-16" , "Authored: Shamovsky, V, 2009-12-16" , "Reviewed: Gillespie, ME, 2010-02-27" ;
